docs.abstract: The German economy shrank in the second quarter and may be headed toward recession. Growth of Chinese factories was the slowest in 17 years.
docs.snippet: The German economy shrank in the second quarter and may be headed toward recession. Growth of Chinese factories was the slowest in 17 years.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — In ominous signs of the damage being done by the trade war between China and the United States, data released on Wednesday indicated that the German economy was hurtling toward recession and that growth at Chinese factories was slowing at a pace not seen in nearly two decades.

headline.main: Germany Nears Recession and Chinese Factories Slow in Trade War Fallout

docs.abstract: Stop-motion animation is a great way to bring toys and other objects to life — and learn the basics of filmmaking.
docs.snippet: Stop-motion animation is a great way to bring toys and other objects to life — and learn the basics of filmmaking.
docs.lead_paragraph: Stop-motion animation has been around since the 1800s and still flourishes in the works of studios like Aardman Animations, the force behind “Wallace & Gromit” and other creations. With stop motion, you make an inanimate object “move” by snapping a photo and then stopping to subtly adjust the object’s position before taking the next shot. When enough photos of these gradual movements are captured, you run them together as a video that shows the object seeming to propel itself.

headline.main: Make Your Own Animated Movies, Frame by Frame
headline.print_headline: Making Animated Movies, Frame by Frame

docs.abstract: Seeking new markets, the Arab kingdom plans to buy 20 percent of the oil-related businesses of India’s biggest company, Reliance Industries.
docs.snippet: Seeking new markets, the Arab kingdom plans to buy 20 percent of the oil-related businesses of India’s biggest company, Reliance Industries.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI, India — Underscoring its desire for stronger ties to India and the country’s 1.3 billion people, Saudi Arabia’s state-owned oil giant is buying 20 percent of the petroleum-related businesses of Reliance Industries, one of India’s biggest companies.

headline.main: As Saudis and Indians Grow Closer, a $15 Billion Deal Blooms
headline.print_headline: Saudis Draw Closer to India With a $15 Billion Deal

docs.abstract: As fake and illegitimate texts proliferate online, books are becoming a form of misinformation. The author of “1984” would not be surprised.
docs.snippet: As fake and illegitimate texts proliferate online, books are becoming a form of misinformation. The author of “1984” would not be surprised.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In George Orwell’s “1984,” the classics of literature are rewritten into Newspeak, a revision and reduction of the language meant to make bad thoughts literally unthinkable. “It’s a beautiful thing, the destruction of words,” one true believer exults.

headline.main: Paging Big Brother: In Amazon’s Bookstore, Orwell Gets a Rewrite
headline.print_headline: Big Brother Is Botching: Orwell Gets a Rewrite
